html.body: ONTOX_LL0002_001 Cholesterol Biosynthesis Pathway This pathway was constructed based on the Brown et al 2021 book chapter (Cholesterol Synthesis), combined with the Reactome Cholesterol Synthesis pathway (DOI:10.3180/R-HSA-191273.7) and the WikiPathways WP4718 (Cholesterol metabolism with Bloch and Kandutsch-Russell pathways - Homo sapiens). A gene regulatory network was added with ends on phenotypes. All edges were annotated with the correspondent sources. Curator: Luiz Ladeira, Biomechanics Research Unit, GIGA In Silico Medicine, University of Liège - Liège, Belgium. Sources: Brown, A. J., Coates, H. W., and Sharpe, L. J. (2021). Cholesterol synthesis. In Biochemistry of Lipids, Lipoproteins and Membranes (pp. 317–355). Elsevier. https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-0-12-824048-9.00005-5 Rozman, D., and Jassal, B. (2015). Cholesterol biosynthesis [Data set]. Reactome - a curated knowledgebase of biological pathways. https://doi.org/10.3180/R-HSA-191273.7 Denise Slenter, Eric Weitz, and Kristina Hanspers. (2022, December 8). Cholesterol metabolism with Bloch and Kandutsch-Russell pathways (Homo sapiens)—WikiPathways. https://www.wikipathways.org/index.php/Pathway:WP4718

-- "Cytosolic HMGCS1 synthesises HMGCoA for cholesterol synthesis, whereas the related mitochondrial HMGCS2 produces HMG-CoA for ketogenesis and stimulates fatty acid oxidation." DOI: 10.1016/B978-0-12-824048-9.00005-5 -- Localized to the Nucleoplasm, Cytosol In addition localized to the Plasma membrane https://www.proteinatlas.org/ENSG00000112972-HMGCS1
IDI2 might catalize this reaction as well, however ther is no data supporting its occurrence in hepatocytes. https://www.proteinatlas.org/ENSG00000148377-IDI2/tissue/liver
